## Precedence
1. Product safety/compliance constraints
2. Monorepo and boundary rules
3. Platform architecture rules
4. Platform coding rules
5. Testing and release rules
6. GitHub Actions CI rules
7. Service/plugin-level feature rules

If two rules conflict, choose the stricter rule and document the decision.

## Platform Contract
- Build chat-first user flows as the baseline UX.
- Implement services as plugins that execute through policy-controlled command/action interfaces.
- Keep web and mobile behavior parity through shared contracts and shared compliance controls.
- Block release when architecture, quality, or compliance rules are unmet.